PEGZ: THE MASTER PROJECT BIBLEI. PROJECT VISION & RULESHigh Concept: A "crazy-looking," high-contrast reinvention of Peg Solitaire featuring living, grotesque characters and hazardous themed boards.Mandatory Aesthetic Rules (The "Vibe"):Contrast: Neon (Toxic Green, Pink, Blue) vs. Industrial Gritty Darks.Characters: "Crazy" and distorted. No standard pegs. Use eyeballs, fangs, and melting slime.IP Safety: Capture the Friday After Next vibe (Corner stores, holiday chaos, pursuit) without using protected names or likenesses.II. THE CORE GAMEPLAY (Logic & Scripting)Triangular Grid Logic: Jumps must skip one occupied hole into one empty hole.Winning: Only one PEG remains.Unique Chaos Mechanics:Slick Surfaces (Ooze World): Landing in a "Slick" hole triggers a momentum slide to the next available hole in the same direction.Contamination (Bio Lab): Landing in a Red Zone locks the PEG for 1 turn.Shadow Jump (Haunted): Ability to jump over two pegs at once.Re-Gift (Urban): Sacrifice a move to bring one removed peg back to the board if only two remain.The Boss Mechanic: The Titan PEGIn the final levels of each world, the last PEG "Awakens." It moves independently every 2 turns. The player must trap the Titan in a corner or a hazard zone to perform a final execution jump.III. THE WORLD THEMES (LEVELS 1-12)ThemeLevel NameKey Mechanicüß™ Bio LabThe Petri DishContamination / Shatterü¶á HauntedThe Red Velvet HauntShadow Jump / Steam Ventsü§Æ Ooze WorldToxic SpillwaySlick Surfaces / Slime TrailsüéÅ Urban ChaosCatch the Sack SnatcherHigh-Value Zones (HVT)üéÅ Urban ChaosThe Nutcracker GambitRe-Gift AbilityIV. VISUAL & AUDIO ASSETS (The "Juice")Shaders & VFX:Glass/Liquid: Bio-Lab pegs use a refraction shader with a sloshing liquid interior.Slime Trails: Slick slides leave a "smear" decal on the board.Shadow Blur: Haunted jumps leave a purple/black "echo" trail.Audio Manifest:Capture Sounds: Bio (Shattering glass), Haunted (Ghostly gasp), Ooze (Hollow PLOP), Urban (Breaking window